items.name: PhotoMaxUltraV1
items.description:
This is a model mix that focuses on real photos with NSFW content. It is trained with many women body but can still make good men body. The goal is to make sharp, natural-light real photos that normal people take with their DLSRs.

Please use vae-ft-mse-840000

Warning! This model is extremely horny. Check out Hassan's page for trigger words.

This model is mixed mainly with Hassansblend 1.2 and DeliberateV2, with many other small mixes, so it has an extremely great variety and potential.

Most prompts for photo real will work; I copied some of the prompts I see here, and they all work great. It works even better if you start the prompt with "A photo of..." since SD is trained this way.

It can do all the good stuff in hassansblend1.2 like tenticle sex and reverse cowgirl in better colors.

It makes good low light photos with Theovercomer8's Contrast Fix LORA 1.5 version. (Model works without Theovercomer8's Contrast Fix LORA; just results will be brighter.)

Also, shout out to PureErosFace_V1! This inversion can make sexy Asian faces easily!

Check out my Twitter to see all previous works using this model.

Have fun!

items.name: WonderMix
items.description:
Merged model with additional fine-tuning for variety and quality. Midjourney-esque with the ability generate highly detailed photo-realistic images/still frames

Like photorealism? Try my new fine-tune 'Lomostyle'

Capabilities

  • Complex 3D renders

  • Photorealistic images

  • NSFW/SFW generations (use tags: nsfw, sfw in prompt)

  • Abstract art

  • Cartoon stills

  • Landscape photography

  • High compatibility with LoRA models

  • Designed to handle light AND complex prompts.

Hardcore generations are also possible but, that wasn't the main focus of this model. There are much better models for this use case, unless you're looking for a more stylized/artistic hardcore generation.

Limitations

  • Anime (Future updates will add Anime capability.)

  • Occasionally the nsfw/sfw tags don't trigger. This can usually be addressed by:

    • Moving the sfw, nsfw tags towards the beginning or end of the prompt.

    • Using attention/emphasis ((sfw)), or (nsfw:1.2)

  • Strong VAE recommendation. (this is due to fine-tuning)

Models used in the merge

Models used in the merge are included in the version description bellow.

Check out my other models

  • Doomer Boomer - https://civitai.com/models/118247?modelVersionId=128239

Futoku No Guild / Immoral Guild - All-in-One
items.description:
The silly female cast from Futoku no Guild / Immoral Guild anime :-)

How to use
Use the character name followed by 1girl for the girls and 1girl OR 1boy for Noma.
On NAI this LoRA was trained on this was enough but it seems like on more styled variants like AOM2 you also have to add negatives to avoid traits from other characters spilling over.
For prompt samples please see the images.

Recommended strength is anywhere between 0.75 to 1.00 depending on prompt, model and character.

Misc
512 resolution trained on NAI without noise offset option for best LoRA compatibility. Dataset based on screencaps from the TV-release. Tested on NAI + AOM2.

All images are raw untouched txt2img generations (slightly cherrypicked).

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

items.name: Attack on Titan LoRA
items.description:
Creating these models takes time, money, and effort and it's great when that effort is rewarded. If you really like it you can buy me a coffee ☕.

If you like this model please consider checking out some of my other projects. I've made LoRAs to emulate the style of Super Crooks, Fullmetal Alchemist, Death Note, Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse, Cyberpunk: Edgerunners, Trigun: Stampede, and Chainsaw Man.

This is Just a LORA that emulates the style of the show. Depending on the subject you're trying to create, you'll need to play around with the strength. 0.65 strength seems to work best. All these images were created with Dreamshaper and Deliberate as the models. X-formers is on.

I trained it on around 18,000 still images from the show, so it's quite good at emulating the style. No need to give it a particularly lengthy prompt these images were generated with really simple prompts.

This LORA mixes well with others as well. So if you want a trained character/person in the Attack on Titan style that's possible. If you have any questions, comments, or concerns feel free to send me a message. I'm happy to chat about my methodology.

Going forward I'm going to upload the training data for all my models. Gathering these images in this quantity isn't something everyone in the community can do, so providing them will give model makers stronger tools.

items.name: Protogen LoRA
items.description:
A LoRA trained on many images of Protogens in order to get them as accurately as can be, what else can be said?

IMPORTANT: The AI will always struggle with the visors first time, they are very easy to inpaint, here is how:

Send image to inpaint. Enable LoRA in the img2img tab as well. Set denoise strength anywhere from 0.65 to 0.85, adjust accordingly. Make sure the positive prompts only have "protogen, protogen face, protogen visor" in them and nothing else. Mask only the visor portion. Make sure setting is on original, and masked image only.

Activation keywords are: protogen, protogen visor, protogen face
Features three different versions:

protogenv2-hard - Trained on 3200 steps, more "canonically" accurate to proto designs and training data

protogenv2-medium - Trained on 2300 steps, might be more lenient towards nsfw and more creative designs, includes a lesser trained epoch as well

protogenv2-soft - Trained on 1900 steps, may be even more creative and lenient, however it may not always be the most correct

No activation tokens are required to use these models.

If unwanted rigging is appearing, try adding machinery to the negative prompt (sometimes I need >1.5x emphasis to get it to go away).

These LoRA were trained at 960x960 for finer detail, so they should also work well for highres fix upscaling.

v5 Series

The v5 series is mainly intended to imitate the style, although it can assist in Ichiso character feature recall.

v5-NAI model

Unless you're generating on a model very closely related to NAI, compatibility won't be quite as good as a LoRA trained directly on your preferred checkpoint, so weights between 0.4 - 0.8 are a good starting point. If combining with other LoRA models, you may need to use lower weights.

On Anything v3-1 about 0.6-0.8 is usable for initial generation with upscale at 0.6 weight with no LoRA, and around 0.4 with another LoRA. YMMV.

v5-Counterfeit model

I recommend using weights between 0.4-1.0, depending on how stylized you want it to be. If combining with other LoRA models, or using with models besides Counterfeit, you may need to use lower weights.

v10 Series

The v10 series is slightly more focused on character feature recall. However, as a result these can be harder to use with more artifacting and/or extraneous features appearing. I recommend using v5 if you don't intend to depict Ichiso ship girls.

Base/remodels forms were tagged with no overlaps. So a Yuudachi Kai Ni image was not tagged with "yuudachi \(kancolle\)", only "yuudachi kai ni \(kancolle\)". As such, you can prompt for a specific form of an Ichiso ship girl by prompting for the specific form and putting alternate forms in the negative if needed (see also: example Yuudachi image in v10-Counterfeit).

Ariake, Yuugure, and Shigure Kai San are still difficult since they have 5, 2 and 3 images in the training set respectively, and little/no representation in base model training sets. Everyone else works fairly well to very well.

v10-AnyPastel model

This model is intended to be widely compatible with many anime models, but I can't guarantee it will work on your favorite merge (AnyPastel is merged from Anything-V4.5, NAI and PastelMix). For those interested I have a comparison of some select models' performances here.

If using on AnyPastel directly try weights from 0.6-0.9.

For other models, or combining with other LoRA/etc., try starting at 0.6 and lowering if the quality is not good.

v10-Counterfeit model

Weights between 0.4-0.8 seem to work well on Counterfeit-V2.5. If combining with other LoRA/etc., you may need to use lower weights.

Dataset

About 338 images of artworks by Kujo Ichiso were scraped from Danbooru, Pixiv, Twitter, and Kancolle Wiki. Some artworks were rotated to be more upright orientation. Duplicates, or closely related images (for instance, intermediate drafts of later artworks, crops of other artworks) were pruned. Most text was cleaned or cropped out. Images containing multiple characters were selectively segmented and cleaned to create single character images where feasible.

Tagging was done via wd14-swinv2-v2 with threshold 0.15. KanColle character tags were manually curated afterwards.

items.name: Hiyori / ヒヨリ / 히요리 / 日和 (Blue Archive)
items.description:
Tsuchinaga Hiyori (Blue Archive)

槌永ヒヨリ (ブルーアーカイブ) / 츠치나가 히요리 (블루 아카이브) / 槌永日和 (碧蓝档案)

Usage

  • Use any or all of the following tags to summon Hiyori: hiyori, 1girl, hair over one eye, side ponytail, aqua eyes, hairclip, halo

  • For her normal outfit: cabbie hat, black sweater, white capelet, white skirt, belt, long sleeves, thigh pouch, kneehighs, loafers, black footwear

    • Without cape: remove white capelet, add grey shirt, collared shirt, wing collar

    • Without sweater: in the negative prompt, use white capelet, grey shirt, collared shirt, wing collar

    • For some reason, the model usually fails to render the black stripe on her skirt, despite being quite accurate otherwise. 😔

  • For her daydreaming expression: smile, naughty face, nervous smile, open mouth

  • For crying:

    • Mild: tearing up, closed mouth, wavy mouth

    • Moderate: crying with eyes open, flustered, tears, wavy mouth, open mouth

    • Maximum: closed eyes, crying, bawling, tears, flustered, (wide open mouth:1.3)

  • Sweater lift: sweater lift, clothes lift, lifted by self, midriff, navel

    • Optional: weight conscious

  • Accessories:

    • weapon case, strap, sling for her rifle case

    • ammunition belt, bullet for her ammo belt

    • fashion magazine, book for her magazines

      • The AI will struggle to render a recognizable magazine cover

    • backpack, holding straps for her equipment pack

The AI may be stubborn with trying to always show her with a scarf or lifted shirt, since she has many images with them. Try using the following negative prompt to counteract this behavior: (black sweater, collared shirt, white cape, grey shirt, white scarf, detached collar:1.2)

Not all tags may be necessary.

I try to avoid overfitting my LoRAs. As a result, your prompt might require more tags to perfectly reproduce the character, but in exchange the model should be much more flexible when changing clothing or hairstyles and mixes well with other LoRAs and art styles. I recommend setting weight to 1.0 and using some of the tags provided above.

私はLoRAモデルのオーバーフィッティングを避けるようにしています。そのため、キャラクターを完全に再現するには、より多くのタグが必要になる場合がありますが、その代わり、モデルはキャラクターの衣服や髪型の変更に柔軟に対応でき、他のLoRAモデルやアートスタイルとも相性が良くなります。必要に応じて、重みを1.0に設定し、上記で提供したタグのいくつかを使用することをお勧めします。

저는 LoRA 모델을 오버피팅하는 것을 피하기 위해 노력합니다. 그 결과로, 캐릭터를 완벽하게 재현하기 위해서는 더 많은 태그가 필요할 수 있지만, 대신 모델은 캐릭터의 의상이나 머리 스타일을 쉽게 변경할 수 있으며, 다른 LoRA 모델 및 아트 스타일과도 잘 어울립니다. 가능한 태그 중 일부를 사용하고, 가중치를 1.0으로 설정하는 것을 권장합니다.

我尽量避免LoRA模型的过拟合。因此，你的提示可能需要更多的标签来完美地复现角色，但是相应地，该模型在更改角色服装或发型方面更加灵活，与其他LoRA模型和艺术风格混合得更好。我建议将权重设置为1.0，并使用上面提供的标签中的一些。

Refer to https://huggingface.co/khanon/lora-training for other Blue Archive characters, training parameters, and datasets.

items.name: Spy Family LoRA
items.description:
Creating these models takes time, money, and effort and it's great when that effort is rewarded. If you really like it you can buy me a coffee ☕.

If you like this model please consider checking out some of my other projects. I've made LoRAs to emulate the style of Super Crooks, Fullmetal Alchemist, Death Note, Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse, Cyberpunk: Edgerunners, Trigun: Stampede, Attack on Titan, and Chainsaw Man.

This is Just a LORA that emulates the style of the show. Depending on the subject you're trying to create, you'll need to play around with the strength. 0.65 strength seems to work best. All these images were created with Dreamshaper and Deliberate as the models. X-formers is on.

I trained it on around 8,000 still images from the show, so it's quite good at emulating the style. No need to give it a particularly lengthy prompt these images were generated with really simple prompts.

This LORA mixes well with others as well. So if you want a trained character/person in the Spy X Family style that's possible. If you have any questions, comments, or concerns feel free to send me a message. I'm happy to chat about my methodology.

Going forward I'm going to upload the training data for all my models. Gathering these images in this quantity isn't something everyone in the community can do, so providing them will give model makers stronger tools.

items.name: POV Breast Grab
items.description:
Update (3/14/2023) - V2 Release

  • This is the release of Breast Grab V2 - 30 pictures were added to the dataset. It was re-trained and a trigger word was added to improve consistency.

  • I suggest using this LoRA at 0.7-1.0 weight for best results.

  • The trigger word is povbreastgrab

  • Make sure to always add povbreastgrab, pov hands, breast grab with the LoRA to properly activate it.

  • It helps the AI if you add a breast size - It also helps if you add nipples to the prompt but you don't have to.

  • CivitAI changes the name of the LoRA - If you copy and paste the prompt exactly from the previews - It will not work.

  • After that you can add other descriptive tags (pov, deep skin, huge breasts, large breasts, medium breasts, from below.)

  • Use CLIP SKIP 2.

Known Issues

  • Sometimes the arms will fuse together or her arm will bend backwards but you can fix this by just adding 1boy.

  • Try lowering the weight of the Breast Grab LoRA when using with character LoRAs. 0.6-0.7 worked best for me.

  • If you don't add nipples to the prompt - It will try to generate the hands over the top of them but sometimes it will generate the hands from beneath and her breasts just won't have nipples.

This was trained on NAI model. I have no idea if it works with realistic models. It works perfectly on some models and some others don't.

Embeds and LoRAs used

Bad Prompt - Giovanna - Every other character seen is in my profile.

Follow me on Twitter for updates- https://twitter.com/TrueHeroBang

Everything I'm making will always be free but if you want to show a little bit more support, you can buy me a coffee - https://ko-fi.com/ekune

items.name: Mk4 Toyota Supra
items.description:
This is a Lora for the MK4 Toyota Supra. There will be more updates to come. The initial batch of training data is relatively limited in scope, but it was all trained on 768x768 images, so it should be high quality. For v1, you can leave the weight at 1, if you have v1.1 I recommend keeping the weight around 0.6-0.7, the higher you go, the more "hdr" it looks, which isn't what I'm going for. I highly highly suggest using the realistic vision checkpoint, found here:

https://civitai.com/models/4201/realistic-vision-v13-fantasyai

But I also would like to see images from your favorite checkpoints as well!!

You can prompt it for front, side and back photos, some of the angles like back and side can get confused, but you will always get the side of the car you want! Check out the prompts in my images for ideas of how to get the most out of this model, and let me know if you have any ideas for future versions!!

My seventh Overwatch LORA. Focused on original appearance.

  • Headgear - Head acessories besides blue visor tint are glued and you have to really try to take them off , if you add cyborg, earrings, forehead jewel, headgear, jewelry, necklace, visor into negatives you might just get lucky and get rid of most of it.

If you liked my work, you can donate here.

Review and comment with your experiences, I would appreciate whatever feedback you can provide in order to continue improving my technique.
